title: Advanced Diploma in Mastering Elite Digital Marketing for Consultants
headline: Start your very own digital marketing agency by applying these core skills in this free online course.
description: Explore how to start a digital marketing agency and position yourself as an expert in this field. This free online course will show you how to attract more customers for your clients. We will guide you, step by step, on how to get into the right mindset to achieve success. Discover how to find your first clients and set up automated systems for client acquisition. Then, we'll show you how to master cold calling and managing ads with ease.
courseDescription:
Do you want to have the freedom to work anywhere in the world or the comfort of your home? Do you want to be your own boss and work on your terms? Do you want financial freedom? If you answered yes to any of these questions, digital marketing might just be the right line of business for you. You don't need to be an expert in creating ads or have prior marketing experience to become a digital marketer. You don't even need lots of money to get started. You'll be surprised how easy it is to build your digital marketing agency and how many businesses are looking for help to bring in new customers. Having the right mindset is essential. We will start by helping you rewire your thinking for maximum success. Mastering the fear of rejection is vital. And getting butterflies when calling businesses to offer your services is normal and part of the process. Learning how to approach companies and convince them that you can help them make money will boost your confidence. Then, you need to understand how to target specific industries that will most likely want to know how you can help them. Finally, this course will teach you to find hundreds of clients willing to work with you. In as little as thirty days from completing this course, you can be working with your clients.

Starting a digital agency is exciting, and learning to set up your website, professional email, and productivity hub is exhilarating. The course teaches you how to prospect for potential clients using Google, Facebook, Yp.com and other sites where people are already advertising. Learn to do video audits where you show prospects what they're missing in their ads or web pages, causing them to lose clients and allow you to position yourself as an expert. We will introduce you to helpful tools to find contacts, automate emails, schedule appointments and send leads to your inbox. Don't worry if you are unsure what to say in your emails! You will get access to templates that already contain what you need to write, and you can copy, paste, and tweak the emails for each prospect. Are you uncertain what to say during a phone call? No problem! Learn the psychology of cold calling, making anyone who answers the phone comfortable talking with you. We supply the scripts of what to say each step of the way to help you conquer your fear. From prospecting to discovery call to the moment you do an online presentation using Zoom, Google Meets, or your preferred digital platform, you will know what to do and what to say.

Become familiar with Google Ads, Local Service Ads, and SEO. Learn how to create and promote your clients' ads, how to optimize the keywords people use when searching for your service and how to perform ad remarketing. With Google Ads, the landing page is critical for converting leads. You will be surprised to learn how many businesses are advertising on Google but don't have a landing page. Learn how to design landing pages that will motivate leads to take action and become customers. You will also learn to create and launch Facebook Ads, target specific audiences and how to optimize your Facebook Ads. Master the skill of tracking your ads and how they perform using a variety of different tools. Towards the end of the course, you will learn how to scale your agency. Understand the benefits of working with a white label agency and learn to outsource work to independent contractors. We have prepared everything for you in step by step guides. All you need to do is follow every action closely. So if you are ready to make the change and learn how to start and scale your very own digital marketing agency, then don't be left behind and take action today!

Start Course Now

  • Lesson Summary

  •  There are 4 stages of learning that we go through to develop any new skill:
    • Unconscious Incompetence: You don’t know that you don’t know.
    • Conscious Incompetence: You practice the skill, but you aren’t very good. You learn fast at this stage because the less you know, the greater the room for improvement.
    • Conscious Competence: You have a skill, but it is not yet consistent and habitual. You need to concentrate on performing, and improvement is difficult.
    • Unconscious Competence: The skill is habitual and automatic. 
  • The Dilts pyramid is a model of personal change that goes from one level to another. Changing something on a higher level would necessarily change things on the lower levels.
  • Conscious Mind: This is your conscious awareness. This is where we create meaning. We can attach whatever meaning we choose to any experience. Our past experiences give us a map of the world from which to operate.
  • Unconscious Mind: This controls and governs all of our experiences. Whatever your conscious mind assumes and believes to be true, your subconscious mind will accept and bring to pass. Think positive, and positive thoughts will follow. Think negative, and negativity will follow.

  • Lesson Summary

  •  THE CLIENT ACQUISITION SYSTEM:
    • Leads: To do outreach, you must have leads that you can market to.
    • Outreach: Once you have your lead list, you can create an outreach strategy to contact those business owners with methods such as cold email, DM, Facebook Ads, cold calling, or direct email.
    • Discovery Call: Some of the businesses on your lead list are interested in learning more. This is where you position yourself as the expert and determine if they would be a good fit for your agency.
    • Presentation + Close: This is where you walk them through a screen share presentation showing how you will get the results. You then close them on a 3, 6 or 12-month contract.
    • Collect Payment: After the client signs an agreement, you send an automated recurring monthly billing invoice via waveapps.com. Very important to make sure it’s a recurring invoice.
    • Onboard Client: After the client signs the agreement and pays the invoice, you send over welcome emails that pre-frame how your relationship will go. This sets your hours of operations and the best way to get a hold of you. This also includes an email requesting client company information for ads and any ad account login info needed.
    • Campaign Launch: This is where you’ve created the ads via Google or Facebook, and you’re ready to launch. Launch time from when a client pays the invoice to launch should be within two weeks.

  • Lesson Summary

  • Things to remember when using LinkedIn:                                                     
    • LinkedIn is the biggest BB Networking Platform online.
    • People are on LinkedIn to network and do business.
    • Understand that there’s no perfect outreach formula.
    • Remember, you are having a conversation, YOU ARE NOT SELLING.
    • People want to feel a sense of significance and importance.
    • Don’t just copy and paste your messages word for word, follow the structure.
    • Add your own unique twist to the templates.
    • Can use LinkedIn Helper, Lead Connect, Meet Alfred.
    • Posting articles/content will help with the authority and credibility of your agency.
